<br>
With a single line respec, I'd drop the parry and raise my axe as high as possible with those points and only then put what's left into parry. If Mythic ever sees fit to make our level 50 BS chant worth taking, it's going to have to be something that will make it worth being even more ineffective as frontline fighters.<br>
<br>
Rogenwald <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/30/02 4:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The problem</span><hr size=1> The problem with 50 BS ?<br>
<br>
There is no upgrade to your really valuable songs (DD, dmg add, speed, mez) over 46.<br>
<br>
The song of rest is seriously flawed : very small regen component compared to the total hit points of a level 50 character (especially buffed), and mostly due to the way regeneration &quot;ticks&quot; work (basically, you have to be sitting, completely still to have a non negligible regeneration - and it doesn't even kick in immediatly, it takes forever to leave combat mode ... ). Even if you are the only skald in the world satisified with our regen chant, the level 50 one isn't even that big of an upgrade over the level 40 one. The only marginal use for this song is solo downtime in PVE. But we are talking about a level 50 song ... do you really need something that will marginally help solo PvE at this level ?<br>
<br>
The level 47+ resist songs are useful, much more so than the song of rest, however to user them really effectiveley, you must have other skalds in the group to cover the &quot;vital&quot; songs (speed, then dmg add). Unless you have an unusual number of skalds in the group, those songs are useful in keep sieges, but then again, you can only protect yourself from one type of damage (and if there are enough enemy PBAE/GTAE casters to require the use of resist songs, odds are that they use a variety of damage types). Thus the request to have those songs grouped like the paladin.<br>
<br>
So, after level 46, you have only improvements to a seriously flawed, almost useless song, and to OK songs that are hard/impractical to use (speed is almost always the priority). The 194 skill points used here can be put imho to a much better usage.<br>
<br>
However, as a &quot;wish list&quot;, I'd really like to have higher BS have more of an impact. A change to our song of rest and resist songs, as requested in the skald TL report, would be definitely welcome. 50 BS *should* be a valid template after all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shilliana@teamskald>Shilliana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/30/02 4:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks</span><hr size=1> Thanks all, I will probably go 46 BS now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=435.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=435.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=435.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=435.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskald